news.title: Thailand's Ratanarak Group takes control of Siam City by buying Jardine Cycle's stake
news.para: Under the deal, Ratanarak unit Sunrise Equity bought 76.1 million shares in Siam City for 160 baht apiece, valuing the cement manufacturer at 47.68 billion baht.

news.title: Sebi issues guidelines for borrowing by category I & II alternative investment funds
news.para: These alternative investment funds (AIFs) are allowed to borrow funds to address temporary funding needs or manage day-to-day operational expenses, with specific limitations.

news.title: Navi Mumbai international airport is moving along pretty quick: Cristiano Ceccato, Zaha Hadid Architects
news.para: In conversation with Ankit Sharma of ETRealty, Cristiano Ceccato, director, Zaha Hadid Architects (ZHA), which had been appointed as the architect of NMIA following an international design competition, talked about the design plans of the project and opportunities they see in India.

news.title: Kalyan-Dombivli civic body set to demolish 10-floor illegal building
news.para: A 10-storey building in Kalyan, Yusuf Height, was determined to be illegally constructed on land designated for a garden and night shelter. After monsoon, KDMC plans to demolish it. The Thane police's EOW filed a complaint against the builder, Salman Dolare, and accomplices for using fake permissions and causing governmental revenue losses.

news.title: Smartworks Coworking Spaces reports Rs 50 crore loss in FY24
news.para: According to the DRHP, the company's net loss stood at Rs 49.95 crore in the 2023-24 fiscal, down 50 per cent from Rs 101 crore in the preceding financial year.

news.title: Madurai civic body suspends five bill collectors for property tax fraud
news.para: The Madurai corporation suspended five bill collectors for decreasing property tax assessments, leading to a revenue loss of Rs 1 crore over two years. The officials were found guilty of accepting bribes to lower taxes without proper authorization. Commissioner C Dinesh Kumar revealed the fraud after an inquiry and called for stringent audits to prevent future irregularities.

news.title: Australia's Lendlease reports $1 billion loss in FY24
news.para: Lendlease, the country's largest property developer, builder and real estate investor, is looking to retreat from its overseas construction business, freeing up upto A$4.5 billion ($3.01 billion) in capital in the process.

news.title: Property demand in UK rises after BoE rate cut: Report
news.para: Rightmove, which says it advertises property for more than nine of every 10 estate agents in the United Kingdom, said buyer enquiries in August were 19% higher than a year earlier, compared with an 11% annual increase in July. British estate agents reports more buyer interest after BoE rate cut

news.title: Residents regret moving into Delhi’s in-situ rehabilitation towers
news.para: In 2022, an optimistic Sujeeta and many of her neighbours in Bhoomiheen Camp slum cluster had gleefully unlocked the flats in Kalkaji Extension allotted to them as part of the in-situ slum rehabilitation scheme.

news.title: Delhi Jal Board to assess 7,000 rainwater harvesting systems
news.para: With groundwater resources overexploited and making up for less than 13% of the daily water supply, a strong network of RWH systems is essential and a viable water conservation method.

news.title: Any software to check sham realty transactions: Punjab & Haryana HC
news.para: “At this stage, the states of Punjab and Haryana are put to notice as to whether there is any software with the sub-registrar enabling them to trace out as to whether the person/vendor in a sale deed is alienating the land within his share or beyond it,” the HC has ordered.

news.title: Kolte-Patil Developers' CFO resigns
news.para: ​In a regulatory filing on Saturday, the company informed that Jena resigned on 17 August 2024 to "pursue professional opportunities outside the organization".

news.title: About 700 km of new metro lines made operational in 10 years: Housing minister
news.para: Metro services are now in 21 cities of the country, the housing and urban affairs minister said and added that prior to 2014, the service was operational in only five cities.

news.title: Over two-thirds of grade-A office stock in India is green-certified: Colliers
news.para: The share of Bengaluru followed by Mumbai remained significant, together accounting for over 50% of the leases in green-certified buildings in Q2 2024.

news.title: Kamdhenu Ventures' profit dips 26.05% in Q1 FY25
news.para: Kamdhenu Ventures' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 54.58 crore in Q1 FY25, a dip of 12.25 per cent from Rs 62.20 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Revised deposit norms unlikely to be onerous for HFCs: Crisil
news.para: Along with various other operational measures, the revised norms contain three key amendments pertaining to HFCs accepting public deposits.

news.title: Omaxe's net loss widens to Rs 147.44 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: The total income increased to Rs 385.23 crore in the April-June period of this fiscal year, from Rs 220.85 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing on August 13.

news.title: Construction equipment sales rise 5% to 28,902 units in Q1 FY25: ICEMA
news.para: ​As per the data released by the Indian Construction Equipment Manufacturers' Association (ICEMA), the construction equipment (CE) industry had sold 27,577 units in the same period of the previous fiscal.
